peanut butter cookies
via http://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/peanut_butter_cookies/

Note: this recipe isn't huge; consider doubling

1/2 cup sugar
1/2 cup packed brown sugar
1/2 cup butter, room temperature
1/2 cup peanut butter
1 egg
1 1/4 cup flour
1 tsp vanilla
3/4 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon salt


1 Beat the butter until creamy, 2 minutes. Add the sugars, beat for 2 more minutes. Mix in the egg, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix together the dry ingredients - flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir the dry ingredients into the sugar butter mixture.

2 Wrap dough in plastic and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

3 Preheat oven to 300Â°F. Shape dough into 1 1/4 inch balls. Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten in crisscross pattern with a fork. Bake until light brown, between 12-15 minutes. Cool on baking sheets for a minute; transfer to rack to cool completely.
